The results of PSG measurements are summarized in Table 4. After treatment, there were significantly lower levels of SOL [15.5 (10.0, 18.5) vs 18.5 (11.5, 31.0), P = 0.039) in the acupuncture group than in the sham acupuncture group. In terms of sleep architecture, the percentage of sleep stage N1 (19.65±5.06% vs 24.99±4.60%, P = 0.015) was decreased and that of stage N3 (25.22±5.31 vs 17.88±4.84, P = 0.002) was increased significantly in the acupuncture group compared with the sham acupuncture group. However, no significant differences in the percentage of stages N2 or R were noted between the groups (P > 0.05).Table 4
